      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SATIN AND CASH (9) gave away around eight lengths at one stage then warmed up late to grab second when resuming over this distance at Gosford last start. Lightly raced filly who has returned in better order this prep. Will be hard to hold out down a much longer straight today. COLD GIN (1) was appearing for the first time in almost a year when a respectable third over 1100m at Canterbury last time out. Not sure coming back to 1000m is the best option but that city form looks good in this company. ZOUSIKA (7) raced handy but tired late and missed the frame on debut over 1100m at the Kensington track recently. Did a bit wrong that day so he should take a lot from the experience. OUR LADY PEACE (8) continues to improve with racing. Very fit and from the inside alley makes plenty of appeal. Gap to the next pick VINGT NEUF NOIR (10) who can run a cheeky race while fresh.",
